runs.comm: tossed up from round the wicket and worked away straight to square leg
flatter ball and he bends and goes deep in the crease and pulls wide of square leg
bad ball and rightly put away, drops it too short from round the wicket, Warner rocks back and clubs it over the vacant midwicket region
tucked away behind square for a single
lands on the pads and he clips it straight to midwicket
makes room and chops it just wide of backward point
flatter and quicker and Watson comes forward and defends
flatter and quicker and he rocks back and mistimes the pull to square leg
outside the off stump and he slices it down to short third man
straight and tucks him up for room, Watson made a hint of room to cut and he chops it back to the bowler
not a bad ball but a terrific shot, didn't give much width but Watson made room and slashed it wide of backward point
flatter delivery and defended
flatter one and Warner makes room and slaps it to Afridi at point
pushes it against the turn to midwicket for a single
bashes a full toss to the leg side and Afridi does brilliantly at square leg to dive and save a boundary surely
works this down to deep midwicket
stops on him and gets a leading edge that lobs to the off side

big appeal for an lbw but turned down! Looked like it skidded through and hit his pad in line with the stumps but there may have been an edge, need to see a replay, replays showed the ball hitting the leg stump clean, well
goes back and pulls him down to long-on
stays back and clips it to the on side
goes back at the crease and pulls him to deep midwicket

the youngster has got the Big Fish! Flighted on middle and Watson made a hint of room to slog that away and the ball hits his pads and the umpire is convinced that was hitting, landed in line with leg stump and replays showed it was hitting leg
Hussey gets off the mark with a clip to square leg
cuts and a brilliant stop by Gul a cover point, positive body language from Pakistan here
picks a full delivery and clips it away down to deep midwicket
stops at the crease before delivery and he pushes it down to cover
flatter delivery and he jabs it straight to cover, fielder attacking the ball well
slower through the air and pushed down to long-off
clipped in front of mid-on and it was a wild throw from Ajmal to the keeper

Australia have lost their openers to the sweep! Perhaps a broom would have been a better option than a bat, tossed up on the off stump and it was going through with the line, and Warner was on his knee punish that and was struck on the pads in front of the leg stump
comes forward and defends
defended close to the pads and Kamran got a bit excited
flatter delivery and defended to the off side
doesn't turn and he tucks it down to mid-on
tucked away to the leg side and there was some confusion with the running, the throw to the bowler was wide
flatter and he works this one wide of midwicket
flatter delivery and he works it down to mid-on
lovely shot by Bailey! It was a bit too Bailey used the pace and didn't try to hit it too hard, ;picked the gap between point and short third man
floated on the pads and he works it down to long-on
flat outside the off stump and he cuts him to sweeper cover
fires it full on the stumps and he drills it back to the bowler
plays the reverse sweep and short third man slides and fumbles
flatter and skids through and he tucks it down to long-on
full on the stumps and jammed back to the bowler
quicker one and he can only tuck it down to square leg for a single, good pressure bowling by Malik
he punches it back to the bowler, another dot
flatter delivery and he works it to deep square leg
full on the pads and worked down to long-on
slogs and misses! Nearly took the off stump
Flighted on middle and leg and he works it to midwicket
the googly beats the outside edge!
pushes it cover and he hurries the single, Malik's throw was wide
a pressure relieving six! To some extent, flighted on off and middle and he gets on his knee and slogs over deep midwicket
flighted on middle and leg and tucked to midwicket
confident shout for an lbw! Tried to pull a short one and it spun inwards and hit his thigh, could have hit the stumps, close call

similar ball and shot and he gets his man this time! Lands outside off and spins into the right-hander, Bailey goes back and tries to bludgeon it over the on side and he's hit on the pad, replays showed the ball hitting middle and off
the doosra and he gets forward and squirts to to the off side
flatter delivery and defended down the track
tucks him up for room and he plunges forward to defend
stays back and punches it down the track
tucks him up for room and he can only stab it back to the bowler
The Dilscoop doesn't quite come off! He tries to scoop it over the keeper and fails to make contact with the bat
Hussey tries the reverse sweep and he doesn't make contact as well, hits Akmal's pads and rolls to the off side
on middle and leg and he works it to short fine leg
full toss from round the wicket and he works it away down to deep square leg
flatter delivery and he punches it back to the bowler
bang! He bowled it flat and White bent his knee slightly and thumped it rows back over deep square leg
tossed up on middle and leg and he lofts him forcefully down to long-on
short outside off and he punches it to cover
flatter delivery and clipped to deep square leg
full outside off and driven down to long-off
flatter delivery and punched down to long-off
this was much quicker and he worked it down to deep square leg
Bowls that quicker and he is beaten on the drive

Australia are crumbling here and even 112 looks a long way off! Maxwell gives Hasan the charge and aims to loft it over the off side, hits the splice of the bat and lobs to Hafeez running to his right at backward point
driven wide of cover for a single
flighted outside off, push-driven to long-off
another drive to long-off
straighter, pushed straighter of straight extra cover, Wade wants one right away, but Hussey waits for the ball to cross the man and then runs
Hussey pulls out the shovel, that shot hardly ever goes wrong. The pull-sweep, and Arafat is dozing at deep midwicket, allowing this go for four
and Hussey pings midwicket. Actually clears it. The slog-sweep this time. Right in the slot for him, he opens up the front leg, and sends it into the crowd
goes back and punches it down the track
gets forward and drives to the off side
stays back at the crease and clips it towards midwicket
that's a cracker of a shot! Flatter delivery and he gets on his knee and sweeps him to deep square leg, it was in the air, flat and wide of the fielder
chops the doosra wide of point
flatter delivery and he pushes it to sweeper cover
112 looks a lot closer now, flatter delivery outside off and he reaches out and lofts crisply down the ground, long-on runs across but the shot was too straight
quicker delivery and he steers it to backward point
chops it down to cover point
dabs it down to point
loose delivery from Afridi! Gifted him one down the leg side, it was fired in quick and a gentle tickle sends it to fine leg
short and wide and he chops it down to sweeper cover
first ball of seam, good start by Gul fired in full outside off and Hussey fails to dig it out
fullish in length outside off and driven wide of point, the sweeper mops up
low full toss and he drills it down the ground to long-off
turning out to be a fine over from Gul, straight yorker outside off and Wade failed to get his bat down to squirt it out
bowls another low full toss and all Wade can do is drill it down the ground to long-off, Gul keeping him quiet
awesome bowling by Gul, another yorker lands on the spot, Hussey nearly trips and falls at the crease as he squirts it out back to the bowler
gently paddled down to short fine leg, Australia playing like their target is 112
down the leg side and he tries to paddle it away and Akmal collects it and appeals confidently
floated on the pads and he pushes it down to long-on
shorter in length and he thumps it to deep backward point
comes well forward and he drives him to sweeper cover
timber! Flatter delivery and Wade bravely tries to paddle it from the middle stump, the ball skidded through and knocked back the middle stump
oh well the procession continues! The top spinner, Cummins was beaten for pace and lack of turn and was all over the place, the ball hits his pads as he tries to loft with the angle
and Australia are through to the semi-finals! They have huffed and puffed to get here, Gul bowls it short and Hussey makes a bit of room and slashes it wide of backward point, he punches the air
low full toss and he pushes it down to long-on and it's only a single
Starc miscues the pull off a short ball and Gul runs forward to take the top edge but it lands safe of any fielder
on the pads and tucked away down to square leg
big swing and a miss, pitched up and Starc wanted to deposit that to the Twin Towers (pardon me if I got my direction wrong)
another swing and a miss, full and a touch wide and Starc swishes at thin air
